@c @ifman @unnumberedsec DESCRIPTION
@emph{ZigzagDownLoader} is a download manager:
@itemize @minus
@item
equipped with command line user interfaces (@emph{CLI}), for terminals (@emph{TUI}), graphics (@emph{GUI}) and for internet and web applications (@emph{Web-UI});
@item
handles downloads of some downloaders such as @emph{Aria2}, @emph{Axel}, @emph{Wget}, @emph{RTMPDump} or @emph{cURL}, using its potential (for example, download acceleration);
@item
extracts the URL of the files to be downloaded from file hosting and video streaming services;
@item
downloads @emph{TORRENT};
@item
automatically requests and downloads files via @emph{IRC/XDCC}, without any human interaction via chat;
@item
downloads movies @emph{LIVE} from some television networks
@item
extends web browsers, such as @emph{Conkeror}, @emph{XXXTerm/Xombrero} and, using @emph{Flashgot}), @emph{Firefox};
@item
the @emph{External Application Button} extension integrates ZDL into @emph{Firefox}, @emph{Chrome/Chromium} and @emph{Opera};
@item
using @emph{Cygwin}, it also works in @emph{Microsoft Windows} (CLI and TUI interfaces, also from @emph{Firefox} + @emph{Flashgot} of Windows).
@end itemize

The server and web interfaces, for remote and network control, make it a useful tool for a @emph{Network Attached Storage} (@emph{NAS}). The interfaces are @emph{responsive} and suitable for different devices. In particular, they can also be used as a remote control for launching multimedia files already downloaded or being downloaded, using a web browser on mobile devices.

Furthermore, the Web interfaces (@emph{Web-UI}) and graphics (@emph{GUI}) allow the quick and intuitive search and selection of @emph{files via XDCC}, without having to perform any IRC/chat.
All interfaces allow @emph{live-tv} recordings to be programmed.

But ZDL is also much more, because it can be:
@itemize @minus
@item
combined with other programs or inserted into a script, as a work tool
@item
extended by the user, who can develop new extensions suitable for their purposes
@item
a polyglot system, using different interpreters (for PHP, Javascript, Python, Perl, Awk ...) and Bash tools
@end itemize

ZigzagDownLoader is a "zigzag" program: it is not just a program, it is a laboratory and a system open to new inventions.

